programme.title: Stanley
programme.desc: Stanley name-drops celebrities that have patronized his newsstand to impress Celia and her friends and must put up or shut up when they come to the hotel to watch him have lunch with a movie star he claims to know.

programme.title: Father Knows Best
programme.desc: Jim is convinced that he has one foot in the grave.

programme.title: Wacky Taxi
programme.desc: A Mexican-American, Pepper (John Astin), has big dreams of striking it rich, but very little capital to make those dreams a reality. But one day Pepper quits his factory job and uses his life savings -- such as they are -- to buy a beat-up jalopy, which he transforms into a taxi. He prowls the streets looking for fares, always trying to stay away from the cops, as his business is illegal. His dreams sour, though, when the car is stolen. He must get it back or lose everything.

programme.title: Hollywood Man
programme.desc: A film crew struggles to finish a motorcycle-stunt epic despite repeated threats of sabotage from the mob.

programme.title: The Deadly Companions
programme.desc: When a bank heist goes wrong, outlaw Yellowleg (Brian Keith) inadvertently kills a 9-year-old boy -- the son of saloon girl Kit Tilden (Maureen O'Hara). Plagued by guilt over the shooting, Yellowleg vows to help her bury the boy beside his father in the now-derelict town of Siringo, Ariz. With criminal cohorts Billy (Steve Cochran) and Turk (Chill Wills), Yellowleg embarks on a dangerous journey into Apache territory to lay the boy in his final resting place.

programme.title: Captain Scarlett
programme.desc: Captain Scarlett (Richard Greene) returns to France to discover the Duke of Corlaine (Manolo Fabregas) seizing property and terrorizing those who resist. When Scarlett helps Spanish Princess Maria (Leonora Amar) escape an arranged marriage, he is arrested and placed in chains, along with Pierre Du Cloux (Nedrick Young), whose lands were confiscated, forcing him to become an outlaw. Scarlett and Pierre break out, rescue Maria and set about rousing the peasants to resist the duke's tyranny.

programme.title: The Deadly Game
programme.desc: An American tourist (Lloyd Bridges) becomes involved in espionage when he tries to help a war buddy in Spain.

programme.title: The Kennel Murder Case
programme.desc: Everyone assumes dog-show competitor Archer Coe (Robert Barrat) committed suicide -- except for intrepid detective Philo Vance (William Powell). As Vance investigates, he turns up evidence of foul play that points in every direction; Coe wasn't just disliked -- he was despised. The long list of suspects includes Coe's niece Hilda (Mary Astor) ; his rival, Sir Thomas MacDonald (Paul Cavanagh) ; and his brother. Can Vance sort through the competing motives to find the true killer?

programme.title: White Zombie
programme.desc: Murder Legendre (Bela Lugosi) is the menacingly named zombie master of Haiti. So it's to him that Charles Beaumont (Robert Frazer) goes when he needs help for a twisted plan. Spurned in marriage by Madeline Short (Madge Bellamy), Beaumont has decided on a simple solution: kill Short and bring her back as a zombie. Then she can be his forever. The only problem comes when Legendre keeps the fetching girl for himself -- and her new husband (John Harron) comes to Madeline's rescue.

programme.title: Elvira's Movie Macabre
programme.desc: Guests at the isolated estate of a mad baron, one by one, become the prey of several kinds of ravenous vegetation.

programme.title: The Last Man on Earth
programme.desc: The survivor (Vincent Price) of a global epidemic battles a race of zombie vampires in an adaptation of Richard Matheson's "I Am Legend."

programme.title: The Disappearance of Flight 412
programme.desc: Col. Pete Moore (Glenn Ford) heads a radar testing squad for the Air Force. When two fighter jets disappear under his command while in pursuit of what he believes was a U.F.O., the monitoring plane is made to land by a mysterious government agency known only as Digger Control, supposedly aiming to explain or discredit U.F.O. sightings. Moore, unaware of Digger Control's grounding of the plane, disobeys orders and mounts his own investigation to find the truth about his men.

programme.title: The Last Woman on Earth
programme.desc: A gangster (Anthony Carbone), his wife (Betsy Jones-Moreland) and a lawyer (Edward Wain) have Earth to themselves.

programme.title: Lady Frankenstein
programme.desc: Baron Frankenstein (Joseph Cotten) is hard at work trying to reanimate human tissue when his daughter, Tania (Rosalba Neri), comes home from university with a medical degree and announces that it has always been her intention to carry on her father's work. The baron is thrilled, but no sooner does he successfully reanimate his creature than it kills him and stalks off. Shocked but undaunted, Tania vows to create an even greater monster to destroy the first in revenge.

programme.title: The History of Flight: We Saw It Happen
programme.desc: This documentary chronicles the first 50 years of flight, beginning with the Wright Brothers' first flight in 1903. It includes interviews with a wide range of other pioneers such as Frank Long, Igor Sikorsky, Glen Martin and Eddie Rickenbacker.

programme.title: The Trail Beyond
programme.desc: Fresh out of college, American Rod Drew (John Wayne) is asked to assist in the search for missing people in Canada. Accompanied by Wabi (Noah Beery Jr.), his friend from school, Drew travels north, but quickly gets into a confrontation with a gang of French Canadian outlaws. When the bandits abduct the young Felice Newsome (Verna Hillie), it becomes apparent they're responsible for the other disappearances as well. Luckily, Drew and Wabi are there, determined to find and free the captives.

programme.title: Brothers of the West
programme.desc: Detective Tom Wade (Tom Tyler) has to investigate the truth behind a robbery and murder of a bank president that's being blamed on Tom's brother, Ed (Bob Terry), who is nowhere to be found. Also trying to find out what happened is the bank president's daughter, Celia Chandler (Lois Wilde). She initially suspects Ed, who is actually being held hostage to prevent him from talking. Eventually, Celia realizes that the culprit may in fact be someone who purported to be her father's friend.

programme.title: Chaplin's Art of Comedy
programme.desc: Although Charlie Chaplin became a worldwide superstar and film icon based on hugely popular later films like "The Gold Rush" and "City Lights," the British comedian began his film career for Mack Sennett's Keystone Film Company in 1914. This feature-length documentary consists of footage from Chaplin's early short films for Sennett alongside silent comedy legends Fatty Arbuckle and Mabel Normand, including the 1915 shorts "The Tramp" and "The Bank," which cemented his film persona.

programme.title: Bloomberg Markets: European Close
programme.desc: Thanks to the time difference between the locations, the financial markets in Europe close when the American markets are still in full swing. Bloomberg covers the end of the European trading day with this half-hour show -- which airs in the morning U.S. time -- during the network's "Bloomberg Markets" daytime programming block. The show is hosted by two anchors on separate continents -- Betty Liu in Bloomberg's New York studio and Mark Barton in London -- who discuss the stories that impacted the European markets that day. Overseeing them is Jenkins, the reclusive caretaker of the Library's sleepy little annex in Oregon. Noah Wyle executive produces and recurs as Flynn, the role he played in the movie series.

programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a normal family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate not once, but twice within two years for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian migr. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandros second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be an American family&amp;quot; - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Shermans March), with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all.&amp;quot;

programme.title: Memories Of A Penitent Heart
programme.desc: Combining a wealth of recently discovered home movies, video, and written documents with artfully shot contemporary interviews and vrit footage, Memories Of A Penitent Heart is a documentary that cracks open a Pandoras box of unresolved family drama. Originating from filmmaker Cecilia Aldarondos suspicion that there was something ugly in her familys past, the film charts her excavation of the buried family conflict around her uncle Miguels death, and her search for Miguels partner Robert a generation later. After two years of dead ends, Robert turns up: but hes not the same man. Hes reinvented himself as Father Aquin, a Franciscan monk with twenty-five years of pent-up grief and bitterness. For the first time, a member of Miguels family wants to hear Aquins side of the storybut is it too little, too late? A story about the mistakes of the past and the second chances of the present, Memories Of A Penitent Heart is a cautionary tale about the unresolved conflicts wrought by AIDS, and a nuanced exploration of how faith is used and abused in times of crisis.

programme.title: America's Heartland
programme.desc: Much of the food Americans eat is produced by farmers and ranchers in the country's heartland, but many people don't know how it's produced. "America's Heartland" provides information about the people and processes responsible for the availability of food and fuel across the country and around the world. The show's reporters and producers tell stories in topics that include farm families, consumer issues, animal welfare and crop sustainability. Some episodes also take the show abroad to countries such as Egypt and Taiwan to show the impact American agriculture has on the global economy.
